title: Cowboys snare Raiders workhorse
text:
NRL 2017: Shaun Fensom signs two-year deal with North Queensland Cowboys February 24, 2017 7:01pm by Staff writers Source: FOX SPORTS NORTH Queensland have confirmed the signing Shaun Fensom on a two-year deal after Canberra agreed to release him from the final year of his contract. 
It’s a handy pick-up for the Cowboys, who are light on forwards following the departures of James Tamou and Ben Hannant. 
Fensom, one of the real workhorses in the competition, fell down the pecking order at the Raiders during the 2016 season and found himself playing reserve grade. 
The 28-year-old has made 139 NRL appearances to date and was awarded the Raiders player of the year back in 2011 and 2012. Canberra's Shaun Fensom in action. pic. Phil Hillyard Source: News Corp Australia 
“He’s a very good player and also very experienced,” Cowboys football manager Peter Parr said of Fensom. 
“With the loss last year of James Tamou and Ben Hannant, we have lost a bit of experience, so he ticks a couple of boxes there. 
“He has come to us late in the piece and we were well-prepared to go with the squad we had put in place this season. 
“But we were clear that if an opportunity arose to sign a quality player, then we would pursue that, and Shaun Fensom is a quality player. He plays in a position where we think we need to add some depth.” 
Fensom will begin training with his new club on Monday and will be available to play in round one — against the Raiders. 
Fensom’s departure from the Green Machine comes a day after winger Edrick Lee was also immediately released to take up a deal with Cronulla.
